# Movies App

Android app to browse trending and upcoming movies using the TMDb API. Built with Kotlin using modern Android development tools and architecture.

## Features

- Fetch and display a list of movies from TMDb
- View movie details: title, release date, rating, overview
- Responsive UI with Jetpack Compose
- Clean architecture with separation of concerns

## Screenshots

_Not available_

## Tech Stack

- **Language**: Kotlin
- **UI**: Jetpack Compose
- **Architecture**: MVVM
- **Networking**: Retrofit + Gson
- **Image Loading**: Coil
- **Dependency Injection**: Hilt
- **Navigation**: Jetpack Navigation
- **State Management**: ViewModel + StateFlow

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Android Studio Hedgehog or newer
- Minimum SDK 24
- TMDb API key from https://www.themoviedb.org/

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/ogunjembola/Movies.git
